## Problem

Pick-ticket runs on Sonnet regardless of repo activity. When `git log
--since="24h"` is empty the task is purely mechanical — read metadata,
compare cached scope/risk, rank by risk, write one line — no difficult
judgment required. Paying Sonnet rates for that is wasteful.

## Solution

In `beat.py`, before launching the pick-ticket skill, check whether any
commits landed in the last 24 h:

```python
def _repo_active(project: ProjectConfig) -> bool:
    result = subprocess.run(
        ["git", "-C", str(project.path), "log", "--since=24h", "--oneline"],
        capture_output=True, text=True
    )
    return bool(result.stdout.strip())
```

If `_repo_active()` returns False, pass `--model claude-haiku-4-5-20251001`
(or the current Haiku model ID) to the pick-ticket skill invocation.
Otherwise keep Sonnet.

Add a `pick_ticket_model` field to `ProjectConfig` defaulting to the
current Haiku model ID, so per-project overrides remain possible.

## Acceptance criteria

- `beat.py` uses Haiku for pick-ticket when `git log --since=24h` is empty
- Sonnet still used on active days
- Configurable per-project via `ProjectConfig.pick_ticket_model`
- `test_beat.py` covers both branches (active / idle)
